ZCZC EE66
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 202300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING AN ANTICYCLONE CENTRED BISCAY 1028 WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE EXTENDING N ACROSS THE W OF THE UK. A FRONT WILL APPROACH FAR NWERN
WATERS FM THE W OVERNIGHT WITH THE HIGH PRESSURE SLIPPING AWAY S AND E. THE
FRONT WILL MOV FURTHER EWARDS DURING SATURDAY AND BY SUNDAY MORNING WILL
PROBABLY LIE IRISH SEA TO EERN FITZROY AS A WKN FEATURE. A SECOND FRONT MAY
FOLLOW FM THE W DURING THE DAY TO REACH PLYMOUTH AND BISCAY BY MIDNIGHT.
DURING THE DAY ON MONDAY THE FRONT WILL CONTINUE EWARDS WITH A BROAD RIDGE
OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING FM THE AZORES ANTICYCLONE IN ITS WAKE. EARLY ON
SATURDAY GALES ARE LIKELY TO SPREAD INTO SOLE AND SHANNON BEFORE EXTENDING
E TO AFFECT LUNDY FASTNET AND IRISH SEA. WINDS GRADUALLY EASING FM THE W
OVERNIGHT INTO SUNDAY MORNING. NO FURTHER HAZARDS ARE LIKELY THROUGH THE
REMAINDER OF THE PERIOD
NNNN